1
00:01:36,159 --> 00:01:37,599
Why is it just the two of you?

2
00:01:40,159 --> 00:01:41,560
The Imperial Inspectorate came too quickly.

3
00:01:42,239 --> 00:01:43,079
We lost one man.

4
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,599
Bunch of useless fools.

5
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:51,920
Take the money.

6
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:53,640
Get out of the capital.

7
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:54,640
Yes, sir.

8
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:01,560
Attack!

9
00:02:15,479 --> 00:02:15,840
A Zheng.

10
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:17,000
You and Ning Chen stay here.

11
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:17,439
Got it.

12
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,759
Ping Zi, come with me. After them!

13
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,240
Yes, sir.

14
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:30,000
This technique...

15
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,840
Could it be the Venomous Lord?

16
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:33,479
The Venomous Lord?

17
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,919
This Venomous Lord, you see,

18
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:37,759
is highly skilled with poisons.

19
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,560
And his methods are utterly ruthless.

20
00:02:39,919 --> 00:02:40,919
The martial world despises him.

21
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:42,319
Just last month,

22
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,639
he wiped out an entire household.

23
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:46,000
By imperial decree, we searched the city.

24
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,639
Not a single lead.

25
00:02:49,479 --> 00:02:51,400
Evading the Inspectorate in the capital

26
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:52,560
is nearly impossible.

27
00:02:53,479 --> 00:02:54,759
Someone must be protecting him.

28
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,680
That, I don't know.

29
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,159
However,

30
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,120
every place we could and should search,

31
00:02:59,199 --> 00:03:00,000
we've already searched.

32
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:01,479
Not a single trace.

33
00:03:02,759 --> 00:03:03,879
What about places you can't search?

34
00:03:05,479 --> 00:03:06,400
Places we can't search?

35
00:03:06,759 --> 00:03:07,599
There are way too many.

36
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,240
The Imperial Palace.

37
00:03:09,919 --> 00:03:10,560
The General's Manor.

38
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,759
The Chancellor's Manor.

39
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:12,719
And also...

40
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:16,680
Wait...

41
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:17,599
Boss!

42
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,000
The guy got away!

43
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:20,360
He ran really fast!

44
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,719
Once at the woods, he ditched his horse,

45
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,560
and vanished without a trace.

46
00:03:28,159 --> 00:03:29,000
I have an idea.

47
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:33,879
Ning.

48
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,120
Well...

49
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,800
Are you sure this will work?

50
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:37,840
An old horse knows the way.

51
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:38,719
It can't fail.

52
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:40,560
Wait, boss.

53
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,800
Are we... are we really searching here?

54
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,120
This is the Left Chancellor's Manor!

55
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,840
Search it.

56
00:03:50,479 --> 00:03:51,919
The Venomous Lord fled to the manor.

57
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:54,240
What if he harms the Left Chancellor?

58
00:03:55,039 --> 00:03:55,840
What we're doing is

59
00:03:56,919 --> 00:03:58,439
protecting the Left Chancellor.

60
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,280
A Zheng.

61
00:04:07,879 --> 00:04:08,319
You stay here.

62
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,719
Ask the gatekeeper who owns the horse.

63
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,199
Got it.

64
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:10,719
Ping Zi.

65
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,199
Gather the men nearby.

66
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,080
And bring them to back us up at the manor.

67
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:13,560
Yes, sir.

68
00:04:15,319 --> 00:04:15,759
Chen Zi.

69
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:17,120
You come into the manor with me.

70
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,160
Let's go scout out the situation.

71
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,399
Remember,

72
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:24,199
Don't clash directly with the Chancellor.

73
00:04:25,439 --> 00:04:26,399
Got it.

74
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,639
Make sure you behave once we're inside.

75
00:04:33,079 --> 00:04:34,319
We'll charge in together.

76
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,639
You're from the Imperial Inspectorate.

77
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,639
What brings you here?

78
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:41,879
We received word

79
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,199
that an intruder broke into the manor,

80
00:04:43,439 --> 00:04:44,519
planning to assassinate the Chancellor.

81
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:45,480
There's no time to lose.

82
00:04:45,759 --> 00:04:46,839
We'll go in first to secure the perimeter.

83
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,000
The main force is right behind us.

84
00:04:48,759 --> 00:04:49,639
But...

85
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,360
No buts!

86
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:51,720
The Left Chancellor's safety comes first.

87
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,199
You can't go in.

88
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,120
You can't just barge in like this.

89
00:04:57,759 --> 00:04:58,439
Hey, brother.

90
00:04:58,839 --> 00:04:59,959
We can't go in. Look at this horse.

91
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,519
Fed so well, strong and handsome.

92
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,920
Its feed must be quite special, right?

93
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,279
Of course.

94
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,839
This is our manor's finest premium feed.

95
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:11,560
Fine feed indeed.

96
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,720
And a fine horse.

97
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,839
That bastard

98
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:19,160
is so damn hard to kill.

99
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:21,360
I know I've failed.

100
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,759
I beg you, Chancellor,

101
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,000
give me another chance.

102
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:29,399
If those above weren't pushing so hard,

103
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,040
I wouldn't have resorted to such a move.

104
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:33,480
I have to admit,

105
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,560
that kid

106
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:38,000
is a tough one to kill.

107
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:40,439
When you came back,

108
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,600
you didn't leave any traces, did you?

109
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,360
Rest assured, Chancellor.

110
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,199
Chancellor!

111
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,759
The Imperial Inspectorate is here.

112
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,800
The Imperial Inspectorate?

113
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,160
How is that possible?

114
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:58,399
They claim an intruder broke into the manor.

115
00:06:01,839 --> 00:06:02,720
I realize my mistake.

116
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:03,839
Useless fool!

117
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:06,720
Stay right here and don't move.

118
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:15,720
It's late at night.

119
00:06:16,279 --> 00:06:17,439
The Chancellor toils for the nation,

120
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,360
exhausted in body and mind.

121
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,480
He finally managed to fall asleep.

122
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,000
He must not be disturbed.

123
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,879
Who do you think you are?

124
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:23,680
Out of the way.

125
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,240
Chancellor.

126
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,560
Chancellor.

127
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,120
Silver Guards of the Imperial Inspectorate.

128
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:39,680
Quite the show of authority.

129
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:43,360
Chancellor,

130
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,319
we received a secret report

131
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,240
that an assassin slipped into your manor,

132
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,600
intending to assassinate you.

133
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,480
It seems the Inspectorate's intelligence

134
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:56,279
isn't all that accurate.

135
00:06:56,639 --> 00:06:59,560
I'm perfectly fine, am I not?

136
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,199
Besides,

137
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:05,519
my manor has always been heavily guarded.

138
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,360
What could possibly happen?

139
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,240
Thanks for your concern, Golden Guard Pan.

140
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,480
Gentlemen,

141
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,759
please take your leave.

142
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:15,439
You—

143
00:07:15,879 --> 00:07:17,319
Your safety is paramount, Chancellor.

144
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,839
Should anything happen to you,

145
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:23,399
we could not answer to His Majesty.

146
00:07:24,639 --> 00:07:27,560
If I say I'm fine, then I'm fine.

147
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,519
If anything does happen,

148
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:32,079
I will bear the consequences myself.

149
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,240
There's no need for you to worry.

150
00:07:34,519 --> 00:07:35,240
Steward Ding.

151
00:07:36,079 --> 00:07:36,879
See them out.

152
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:38,160
Yes, sir.

153
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,079
My lords,

154
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:42,759
this way, please.

155
00:07:49,399 --> 00:07:50,560
Seize him at once!

156
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,600
It's you!

157
00:08:02,439 --> 00:08:02,920
Ning Chen.

158
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,560
You know him?

159
00:08:05,519 --> 00:08:06,480
Earlier today on the street,

160
00:08:07,319 --> 00:08:08,560
his carriage ran into me.

161
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,680
Now that you mention it, my lord,

162
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:13,240
I do recall it.

163
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,600
That was because

164
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,519
my horse was startled.

165
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:21,759
You worthless fool!

166
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,759
Can't even drive a carriage properly.

167
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,920
What good are you?

168
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:29,160
Apologize to Silver Guard Ning at once!

169
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:29,839
Yes, sir.

170
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,879
Silver Guard Ning, I am so sorry.

171
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,919
Making you roll on the ground like that...

172
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,399
was entirely my fault.

173
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,960
You're a magnanimous man.

174
00:08:42,279 --> 00:08:44,000
Surely you won't hold it against me?

175
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,720
If you truly can't let it go,

176
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,840
punish me however you wish,

177
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:51,799
I'll accept it.

178
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:54,240
All right.

179
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,480
I suspect you're tied to my attacker.

180
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:00,919
Come back to the Inspectorate with me

181
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:02,519
for interrogation.

182
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:04,159
Suspicion?

183
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:09,919
You can just arrest someone on suspicion?

184
00:09:10,519 --> 00:09:12,240
This is the steward of my manor.

185
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:14,080
Could it be...

186
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,080
that you suspect me as well?

187
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:20,240
My lord, you cannot enter!

188
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,159
My lord!

189
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:28,240
When we were pursuing the assassin,

190
00:09:28,759 --> 00:09:30,039
he abandoned his horse and fled.

191
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:32,200
And this horse,

192
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,519
knowing its way home,

193
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:37,000
led us straight to your manor.

194
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,240
Reporting to Golden Guard Pan,

195
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,360
the gatekeeper has confirmed

196
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:42,399
this horse does belong to the manor.

197
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:46,240
How are you guarding the gate?

198
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:48,519
Chancellor.

199
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:50,399
I couldn't stop it, Chancellor.

200
00:09:53,279 --> 00:09:55,080
You can't even keep track of a beast,

201
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:59,480
letting it wander into the manor at will.

202
00:10:04,799 --> 00:10:05,320
This—

203
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:09,000
Damn it.

204
00:10:10,639 --> 00:10:11,120
By the way,

205
00:10:11,799 --> 00:10:12,759
you said just now,

206
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,840
who confirmed it?

207
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:17,519
You—

208
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,360
Chancellor,

209
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,120
since you are unharmed,

210
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:23,519
this must be a misunderstanding.

211
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,799
We shall take our leave.

212
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:41,480
Chancellor.

213
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:42,919
Your horse.

214
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,360
Chen Zi, what's going on?

215
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:56,600
Judging by that display,

216
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,120
the Venomous Lord is definitely inside.

217
00:10:59,440 --> 00:10:59,879
But this...

218
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:02,919
Boss

219
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:04,320
No way.

220
00:11:04,679 --> 00:11:06,399
Let's ask Old Geng to request a decree

221
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:07,360
to search the Left Chancellor's manor.

222
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,320
The Left Chancellor is deeply rooted in court.

223
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,799
He served the late emperor,

224
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,120
a veteran of two reigns,

225
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,440
and has military merits to his name.

226
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,559
Without evidence,

227
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:17,440
His Majesty won't issue such a decree.

228
00:11:19,559 --> 00:11:20,960
Right now, our only option

229
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,039
is to catch the Venomous Lord first.

230
00:11:23,759 --> 00:11:24,960
Wait, I just can't figure it out.

231
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,480
He's the Left Chancellor of the court.

232
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,559
Why would he shelter

233
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,879
an outlaw like him?

234
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,919
He's the Left Chancellor.

235
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:34,240
He has to keep up appearances.

236
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:36,120
All the dirty work,

237
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,320
the shady dealings,

238
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,200
outlaws are far more convenient to use.

239
00:11:40,519 --> 00:11:41,039
Enough.

240
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:42,159
Stop talking nonsense.

241
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,039
Until we have proof,

242
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,360
every word we say

243
00:11:45,679 --> 00:11:46,960
can be used against us.

244
00:11:47,559 --> 00:11:49,080
Slaughtering innocents like this,

245
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,200
treating human lives like dirt,

246
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,440
I will make you pay the price.

247
00:12:01,519 --> 00:12:02,879
How could you be so careless?

248
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:04,480
It was an emergency.

249
00:12:05,039 --> 00:12:06,759
Please forgive me, Chancellor.

250
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,039
Enough.

251
00:12:08,879 --> 00:12:10,000
Don't let it happen again.

252
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:11,720
Get out.

253
00:12:19,639 --> 00:12:20,320
Right this way.

254
00:12:43,039 --> 00:12:44,919
I know what to do.
